To enable compatibility with an ILI9341 TFT display, you need to do the 
following in the PlatformIO TFT_eSPI library.

#Step 1: 

Go to the User_Setup_Select.h file and comment out line #27, which says 
#include <User_Setup.h> // Default setup is root library folder," and uncomment line 
#76, which says "#include <User_Setups/Setup42_ILI9341_ESP32.h> // Setup file for 
ESP32 and SPI ILI9341 240x320"

|--.pio
   |--build
   |
   |--libdeps
      |--esp32dev
         |--TFT_eSPI
            |- User_Setup_Select.h

#Step 2:
Go to the "User_Setups" folder of the library and find the file called "Setup42_ILI9341_ESP32.h" 
and uncomment line number #14 which says "#define TOUCH_CS 5 // Chip select pin (T_CS) of touch 
screen" to enable the touch of our screen.

|--.pio
   |--build
   |
   |--libdeps
      |--esp32dev
         |--TFT_eSPI
            |-- User_Setups
                |- Setup42_ILI9341_ESP32.h

